  "text": "Our validated ''dorsal'' gene set show an increase in the activating H3 K4 trimethylation marks in the promoter region, compared with the random set of genes, and an overabundance of ''bivalent'' histone-marks at the onset of zygotic transcription ( Figure 5C) , showing that dorsal genes are epigenetically marked prior to transcriptional activation. (Of note, according to the Lindeman et al. dataset [CITATION_1] dharma, one of the earliest transcribed genes in the zebrafish genome [CITATION_2] , carries only H3K27 trimethylation during the time of its transcription. This could be an error in the dataset, but could also suggest a peculiar epigenetic regulatory mechanism at this genomic locus.)",
